threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3115-b , green light, does not turn on , P3V3S5_EN_L missing
threads.message:
this 3115-b board had little water damage , now fully cleaned,   

5v and 3.3v is missing, 

on Q7221 pin5 P3V3S5_EN_L   is missing , but there is P5VS3_EN_L on pin2


P3V3S5_EN_L  taking me  to to U7941


U7941 here is pin voltage 

1=3.49v
2=3.49v
3=3.47v
4=0v


5=0v
6=3.34v
7=0v
8=3.47

any idea why P3V3S5_EN_L missing??

threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3115-b , green light, does not turn on , P3V3S5_EN_L missing
threads.message: P3V3S5_EN_L is supposed to be missing hence the L. So either a short on 3V3 bus or bad 51125 or corroded trace around it.

threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3115-b , green light, does not turn on , P3V3S5_EN_L missing
threads.message: U5010 just controls SMC_RESET so I fail to see how this would prevent power up. If SMC_RESET was messed up there would not even be a green light. Something else got heated and made it work again is my guess.

as soon as i changed the U5010 it works perfectly ... at the very beginning there was corrosion around that U5010...
